==English==
===Etymology===
From the Japanese [[円]] (en), yen.

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛn|-ɛn]]

====Noun====
'''yen''' (''plural:'' '''yen''')

#The unit of Japanese currency, equal to 100 [[sen]].

===Etymology===
From the English yen-yen, "a craving for opium", from the Chinese yIn-yáhn, "opium craving".

====Noun====
'''yen''' (''plural:'' '''yens''')

#A strong desire, urge, or yearning.

=====Synonyms=====
*[[craving]], [[desire]], [[hankering]], [[urge]], [[yearning]]

====Intransitive verb====
'''yen''' ('''yens''', '''yenned''', '''yenning''')

#To have a strong desire for.

